rows.label: tev079201_SEL2021
rows.name: Ask Phoskeran about recent developments.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079201_MSG0001
rows.name:
So you humans moved your souls into mechanical
bodies call mimeosomes and traveled to Mira? *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079201_MSG0002
rows.name: That was an bold move for certain! *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079201_MSG0003
rows.name:
But why not go all the way? *fsssh* Why maintain
purely emotional functions that can only interfere with
your ability to explore a new world?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079201_MSG0004
rows.name:
Plenty of Ganglion members have mechanized their
own bodies, but I've never seen any of them add the
functionality to cry as you humans have. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079201_MSG0005
rows.name:
Was it perhaps some sort of...joke? *fsssh* If so,
I'm surprised at how far you would go for amusement.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079201_MSG0010
rows.name:
*fsssh* When I'm steering my trailer through Primordia
in search of voltant, I occasionally encounter BLADEs.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079201_MSG0011
rows.name:
Sometimes they're battling indigens... Sometimes they're
desperately pounding strange poles into the dirt...
*fsssh* Yes, I've seen all kinds.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079201_MSG0012
rows.name:
But whenever they see an indigen attacking my vehicle,
they almost always come to help. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079201_MSG0013
rows.name:
The other day, they even escorted me to a pleasant
place called a "base camp" so that I could rest and
recuperate. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079201_MSG0014
rows.name:
I am most grateful. *fsssh* The next time I feel an urge
to skip work, I will allow myself to indulge in a nap at
one of your "base camps."[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079201_MSG0019
rows.name:
My explorations have confirmed that there is voltant
to be found throughout this planet. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079201_MSG0020
rows.name:
In Sylvalum, to the north, there blooms a flower known
as the antorus rose that contains a potent voltant
within. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079201_MSG0021
rows.name:
Should you continue north to more distant lands,
you'll find belzadozebu scallions, which contain a
voltant strong enough to bring down giant indigens.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079201_MSG0022
rows.name:
*fsssh* Perhaps your journeys will take you to such
distant lands someday.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079201_MSG0023
rows.name:
If so, I would be honored to receive a large quantity
of toxic items as a souvenir! *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079201_MSG1001
rows.name:
I never imagined that the masked man who stole the
voltant would turn out to be Homer. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079201_MSG1002
rows.name:
Although now that I think back upon it, I do vaguely
recall him asking where our voltant was stored during
one of his lessons. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079201_MSG1003
rows.name:
At the time, I figured he wanted that information in
order to craft some sort of new metaphor or something.
*fsssh* What a shame.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079201_MSG1004
rows.name:
Well, I suppose it wouldn't hurt to pay a visit to this
"prison" place where he is being held and hear him
out. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079201_MSG1005
rows.name:
And if he were to grace me with another of his
thrilling metaphors, all the better! *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079201_MSG1010
rows.name:
I tried using this FrontierNav that your people have
installed. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079201_MSG1011
rows.name:
I was told to develop a route that would traverse all
of Mira so that we might recover its voltant. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079201_MSG1012
rows.name:
It is an incredible hassle. Metaphorically speaking,
it is a hassle on the magnitude of returning to here
from the lowest strata of New LA. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079201_MSG1013
rows.name:
If I were to truly pursue such a plan, I would need to
devote every ounce of strength I possess to finding
good napping points for each step of the route. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079201_MSG2001
rows.name:
The more I think about it, the more I wonder what
Homer was doing there in the first place. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079201_MSG2002
rows.name:
Perhaps he was on a training journey to heighten his
talent for crafting brilliantly clear metaphors? *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079201_MSG2003
rows.name:
Hmm. Risking one's life in pursuit of training... *fsssh*
It's just like the baibai beetle said to be found in
Sylvalum![ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079201_MSG2004
rows.name:
I should have expected no less of the professor.
*fsssh* I must work harder on my own training so as
not to fall behind![ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079201_MSG2005
rows.name:
While the professor is still pursuing his training in
that "prison," I must ask him to teach me the deepest
secrets of crafting metaphors. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]
